Understanding how allele frequency transformations affects trends

Moi Exposito-Alonso

2023-04

Setup allele frequencies

##### Generate some starting allele frequency
p=seq(0,1,0.001)

##### Generate random trajectories independent of start
p1=runif(length(p))

plot(p1-p ~ p, ylab="uniform frequency change (p1-p0)", xlab="starting frequency (p0)")

##### Generate trajectories depending of start
# just drift
N=100
p2=rbinom(length(p),N,p=p)/N

plot(p2-p ~ p, ylab="binomial frequency change from previous state (p1-p0)", xlab="starting frequency (p0)")

# with selection
s=0.5
wAA=1+s*2
wAa=1
waa=1
w_hat=( wAA*p^2 + wAa*2*p*(1-p) + waa*(1-p)^2 )
p3 <- ( wAA*p^2 + wAa*p*(1-p) ) / w_hat
p3=rbinom(length(p3),N,p=p3)/N

plot(p3-p ~ p, ylab="frequency change based on s=0.5 (p1-p0)", xlab="starting frequency (p0)")

hist(p3-p , xlab="frequency change based on s=0.5 (p1-p0)",main = "")

What transformations do to the change in frequency

Scale with starting variance (selection 0.05)

plot((p3-p)/(p* (1-p)) ~ p)

hist((p3-p)/(p* (1-p)) , xlab="frequency change based on s=0.5 (p1-p0)/(p0(1-p0))",main = "")

Scale with arcsin transformation (selection 0.05)

plot(asin(sqrt(p3))-asin(sqrt(p)) ~ p)

Scale with logit transformation (selection 0.05)

plot(log((p3/(1-p1)))- log((p/(1-p)))  ~ p)
